'''Leipzig Miltitzer Allee''' ({{lang-de|Bahnhof Leipzig Miltitzer Allee}}) is a [[railway station]] located in [[Leipzig]], [[Germany]]. The station opened in December 1983 and was closed between April 2011 and 15 December 2013. The station is located on the [[Leipzig-Plagwitz<U+2013>Leipzig Miltitzer Allee railway]]. The train services are operated by [[Deutsche Bahn]], as part of the [[S-Bahn Mitteldeutschland]].

